mylistpackage

Class LinkedArrayListSorted<E extends java.lang.Comparable<? super E>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • mylistpackage.AbstractLinkedArrayMyList<E>
      • mylistpackage.LinkedArrayListSorted<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the Comparable data type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    MyList<E>

    public class LinkedArrayListSorted<E extends java.lang.Comparable<? super E>>
extends AbstractLinkedArrayMyList<E>
    The linked array list data structure containing a sorted list of elements in ascending order. Each elemental data must be a Comparable type. The underlying data structure is an array, but the entity can be operated on same as a linked list. This implies the array is re-sizable.
    Version:
    4.16C
    Author:
    Sam Brendel
    See Also:
    AbstractLinkedArrayMyList

      • binarySearch

        private int binarySearch(E theValue)
        Binary search algorithm that is O(log(n)), and only relevant on a sorted list in ascending order, and assumes the list is not empty. If the data does not exist, a negative index value shall be returned. The negative of this value is where the data would have been found if it existed.
        Parameters:
        theValue - the value to search for.
        Returns:
        the index of the data found, else if not found then the same index number is returned, but negated.
